<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bpmn:definitions xmlns:bpmn="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/MODEL"
                  xmlns:bpmndi="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/DI"
                  xmlns:dc="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DC"
                  xmlns:di="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DI"
                  id="Definitions_ApprovalRoutingEdge" targetNamespace="http://bpmn.io/schema/bpmn">
  <bpmn:collaboration id="Collaboration_ApprovalRoutingEdge">
    <bpmn:participant id="Participant_ApprovalRoutingEdge" name="Edge Case e01 - Approval Routing, Nearest-Bucket Selection and Auto-Approval" processRef="Process_ApprovalRoutingEdge" />
  </bpmn:collaboration>
  <bpmn:process id="Process_ApprovalRoutingEdge" isExecutable="false">
    <bpmn:laneSet id="LaneSet_ApprovalRoutingEdge">
      <bpmn:lane id="L_appr" name="Approver">
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>ManualDecide</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>GwAvailable</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
      </bpmn:lane>
      <bpmn:lane id="L_sys" name="Platform / System">
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Start</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Resolve</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>GwEligible</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Blocked</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>GwThreshold</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>NearestBucket</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>AutoApprove</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>AssignManual</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Reassign</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>PostValueSync</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Route</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>End</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
      </bpmn:lane>
    </bpmn:laneSet>
    <bpmn:startEvent id="Start" name="Stage reached (request approval)">
      <bpmn:documentation>Entry. The configurable approval engine has advanced to a stage and request-approval is invoked for the current vertical (e.g. POST /api/ticket/:id/vertical/:verticalId/request-approval). This edge case isolates how the engine resolves the chain, selects exactly one approver by nearest-bucket, and decides auto vs manual. Fixed example chain: REQ_DEPARTMENT -&gt; PROCUREMENT -&gt; FINANCE -&gt; MANAGEMENT -&gt; null; this diagram zooms the FINANCE/MANAGEMENT selection. [SCOR OE2 Business Rules | ISO 8.4 | source: raphe-routing-approval + raphe-edge-cases e01]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f1</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:startEvent>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="Resolve" name="Resolve approval chain (dept/category/value)">
      <bpmn:documentation>Resolve the RoutingRuleEntry for (requester department, current vertical) - unique key (department, verticalId). Load active candidate approvers from the rule's approverUserIds for that vertical (for FINANCE, all active finance approvers). Per-vertical strategy: Req Department assignee = requester (pinned), approver from rule; Procurement assignee from rule, no auto-approver; Finance approval-only (approver = assignee, FinanceRoutingHelper); Management both from rule. [SCOR OE2 | source: raphe-routing-approval per-vertical strategies]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f1</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f2</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GwEligible" name="eligible approver found?">
      <bpmn:documentation>Guard: candidate pool non-empty after loading active approvers for the vertical AND (for finance) after the eligibility filter below. If the pool is empty at load (no routing rule / no active approver) OR no candidate's effective limit covers the amount -&gt; NO. NO -&gt; BadRequestException 'No eligible approver', the transaction rolls back, the requisition STALLS (blocked) until an admin fixes the routing rule or an approver limit. YES -&gt; proceed to threshold check. [SCOR OE2 | source: raphe-routing-approval errors/edges + e01 empty-pool BadRequestException]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f2</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f3</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f4</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
    <bpmn:endEvent id="Blocked" name="BadRequest - stage blocked">
      <bpmn:documentation>Terminal error state for this stage. BadRequestException is thrown, the approve/request transaction rolls back (no partial state), and the requisition cannot advance past this vertical. An admin must add/correct the RoutingRuleEntry or set an approver's approvalLimit, after which request-approval is retried. No auto-fallback to a default approver (deliberate: silent mis-routing is worse than a hard stop). [SCOR OE2 | source: raphe-edge-cases e01 'no fallback; empty pool -&gt; BadRequestException']</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f3</bpmn:incoming>
    </bpmn:endEvent>
    <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GwThreshold" name="within auto-approval threshold?">
      <bpmn:documentation>Auto-approval guard allowAutoApproval returns true ONLY for the FINANCE vertical AND totalAmountInBase &lt;= approvalLimit. IMPORTANT divergence: the limit used for the auto-approval DECISION comes from the Req Department approver (approvalRequestedTo ?? assignedTo; approver.approvalLimit ?? 200000), which can DIFFER from the per-candidate eligibility limits used in nearest-bucket selection. Boundary: amount exactly == limit auto-approves (inclusive &lt;=). Non-finance verticals never auto-approve. YES -&gt; auto-approve path; NO -&gt; nearest-bucket selection then manual. [SCOR OE2 | source: raphe-routing-approval Finance auto-approval (04) + e01]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f4</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:incoming>f15</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f5</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f6</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="NearestBucket" name="Nearest-bucket approver selection">
      <bpmn:documentation>Select exactly one approver. (1) effective limit per candidate = approvalLimit ?? 200000 (DEFAULT_TICKET_APPROVAL_LIMIT; a configured 0 stays 0). (2) eligible iff effectiveLimit &gt;= totalAmountInBase (inclusive). (3) NEAREST BUCKET = keep only candidates at the MINIMUM eligible limit (reserves high-limit approvers for big tickets). (4) tie-break = least-loaded: urgency-weighted count of non-APPROVED completions across assignedToId + approvalRequestedToId, weights ASAP=4 / SameDay=2 / Within2Days=1 / Within1Week=0; pick the lowest. Returns exactly ONE approver; no fallback; empty after step (2) -&gt; BadRequestException (loops back to the eligible gate as NO). [SCOR OE2 | source: raphe-edge-cases e01 nearest-bucket + raphe-routing-approval step 1-5]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f6</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f7</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="AutoApprove" name="Auto-approve (logged, no second person)">
      <bpmn:documentation>Auto-approval path. Set completion APPROVED, isAutoApproved = true, approvedAt = now; NO approval-requested email is sent; the human OTIF user-stats path is NOT run (auto-approvals do not count toward streaks). Then RECURSE routing to the next vertical (Management), which never auto-approves -&gt; sets AWAITING_APPROVAL + sends the approval-requested email. Auto-approval does NOT complete the requisition. This is the only no-second-person approval path and is always audited. [SCOR OE2 | source: raphe-routing-approval auto sets APPROVED/isAutoApproved, recurse to Management]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f5</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f8</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="AssignManual" name="Assign to selected approver (AWAITING_APPROVAL)">
      <bpmn:documentation>Manual path. Set completion AWAITING_APPROVAL, record approvalRequestedToId = the single nearest-bucket approver, emit TICKET_APPROVAL_REQUESTED notification. First assignment moves the completion NOT_STARTED -&gt; IN_PROGRESS. SoD pre-check: the approver may not be the owner of the requisition/PO (never self-approve). [SCOR OE2 | ISO 8.4 | source: raphe-routing-approval request approval + role-permission-matrix SoD]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f7</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f9</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:userTask id="ManualDecide" name="Approver approves or returns for revision">
      <bpmn:documentation>The approver acts (approval.approve / approval.reject). Authorized = the approvalRequestedToId user OR an assignee with the required designation rank (DESIGNATION_RANK), AND never the user's own requisition/PO (bounded self-approval SoD). Approve -&gt; sets APPROVED + approvedAt in a transaction, updates OTIF stats for assignee + approver (HIT if remainingTime = allowedDuration(priority) - elapsed &gt; 0, else MISS; overdue approval resets the streak to 0), then routes to the next vertical (Management terminal). Reject -&gt; return-for-revision loop to the requester with a mandatory note. [SCOR OE2 | source: raphe-routing-approval approve + raphe-edge-cases e07 OTIF]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f9</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:incoming>f13</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f10</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:userTask>
    <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GwAvailable" name="approver available? (on leave / overloaded)">
      <bpmn:documentation>Operational gate. If the selected approver is on leave / inactive / unable to act, the stage is reassigned or delegated. approver active-status is re-checked per request (deactivation forces logout); an inactive approver cannot hold a pending completion. YES (available, acted) -&gt; route onward. NO -&gt; reassignment / delegation. [SCOR OE2 / OE5 | source: raphe-routing-approval delegation/reassignment on leave + platform-services per-request active-status re-check]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f10</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f11</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f12</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="Reassign" name="Reassign / delegate to qualified approver">
      <bpmn:documentation>Reassignment (approval.reassign) or delegation (approval.delegate): the completion's approvalRequestedToId is moved to another qualified approver (same-or-higher designation rank; not own requisition/PO; eligible by limit if FINANCE). Delegation may be a standing leave rule. The completion stays AWAITING_APPROVAL under the new approver; a new TICKET_APPROVAL_REQUESTED notification fires; audited. Loops back to the manual decision. [SCOR OE2 / OE5 | source: raphe-routing-approval reassign/delegate + role-permission-matrix approval.reassign/delegate]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f12</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f13</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="PostValueSync" name="postValueSync - revert auto-approval on financial change">
      <bpmn:documentation>Revert rule (RA e02). After ANY write to the requisition: recompute total = sum(qty x unitPrice); if changed, reconvert to base via FX. THEN, ONLY if payTerms OR paymentSchedules changed, revert completions where vertical IN (FINANCE, MANAGEMENT) AND status == APPROVED AND isAutoApproved == true -&gt; back to AWAITING_APPROVAL (forces re-approval of the financially-changed requisition). Manual approvals and REQ_DEPARTMENT / PROCUREMENT completions are NEVER reverted. Always emits ticket.updated; the hook never aborts. Reverted stages re-enter request-approval. [SCOR OE2 | source: raphe-edge-cases e02 postValueSync + raphe-routing-approval financial-edit revert]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f14</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f15</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="Route" name="Route to next vertical / complete">
      <bpmn:documentation>On an APPROVED completion (auto or manual), handleRouting advances to the successor vertical and re-enters this whole resolve/select/decide flow for it. Management is terminal (never auto-approves). When the terminal vertical is APPROVED and all completions = APPROVED, approvals are done for the requisition (completion of the overall cycle has its own guard: POST_DELIVERY + matches cleared + no NCR/CAPA block). Every decision (manual + auto) is audited. [SCOR OE2 | source: raphe-routing-approval handleRouting + data-model completion state machine]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f8</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:incoming>f11</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f14</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f16</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:endEvent id="End" name="Approvals resolved for requisition">
      <bpmn:documentation>Terminal. All approval completions resolved (APPROVED) or the stage blocked. Auto-approvals logged, manual approvals OTIF-scored, financial changes correctly forcing re-approval. [SCOR OE2 | source: build-new + RA engine]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f16</bpmn:incoming>
    </bpmn:endEvent>
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f1" sourceRef="Start" targetRef="Resolve" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f2" sourceRef="Resolve" targetRef="GwEligible" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f3" name="no eligible approver -&gt; BadRequest" sourceRef="GwEligible" targetRef="Blocked" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f4" name="eligible pool found" sourceRef="GwEligible" targetRef="GwThreshold" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f5" name="FINANCE and totalAmountInBase &lt;= approvalLimit" sourceRef="GwThreshold" targetRef="AutoApprove" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f6" name="over threshold or non-finance" sourceRef="GwThreshold" targetRef="NearestBucket" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f7" sourceRef="NearestBucket" targetRef="AssignManual" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f8" sourceRef="AutoApprove" targetRef="Route" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f9" sourceRef="AssignManual" targetRef="ManualDecide" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f10" sourceRef="ManualDecide" targetRef="GwAvailable" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f11" name="available - approved/returned" sourceRef="GwAvailable" targetRef="Route" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f12" name="on leave / inactive / overloaded" sourceRef="GwAvailable" targetRef="Reassign" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f13" sourceRef="Reassign" targetRef="ManualDecide" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f14" name="financial field later edited" sourceRef="Route" targetRef="PostValueSync" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f15" name="reverted auto-approval re-enters" sourceRef="PostValueSync" targetRef="GwThreshold" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f16" name="all completions APPROVED" sourceRef="Route" targetRef="End" />
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="NoteRouting">
      <bpmn:text>Isolation of the load-bearing approval rules. Resolve chain -&gt; eligible approver found? (no -&gt; BadRequest, stage blocked, no fallback) -&gt; within auto-approval threshold? (FINANCE and totalAmountInBase &lt;= approvalLimit, inclusive; limit sourced from Req-Dept approver, can diverge from selection limits) -&gt; auto-approve (logged, no second person, recurse to Management) OR nearest-bucket selection then manual. Nearest bucket: effective limit = approvalLimit ?? 200000; eligible iff &gt;= amount; keep the MINIMUM eligible bucket; tie-break least-loaded urgency-weighted (ASAP=4 / SameDay=2 / Within2Days=1 / Within1Week=0). Reassignment/delegation on leave. postValueSync reverts an auto-approved FINANCE/MANAGEMENT completion to AWAITING_APPROVAL only when payTerms or paymentSchedules change.</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:association id="Assoc_ApprovalRoutingEdge_1" sourceRef="NearestBucket" targetRef="NoteRouting" />
  </bpmn:process>
  <bpmndi:BPMNDiagram id="Diagram_ApprovalRoutingEdge">
    <bpmndi:BPMNPlane id="Plane_ApprovalRoutingEdge" bpmnElement="Collaboration_ApprovalRoutingEdge">
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="Participant_ApprovalRoutingEdge_di" bpmnElement="Participant_ApprovalRoutingEdge" isHorizontal="true">
